SIMPLE: frostbite
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frostbite
<hw>Frost"bite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The freezing, or
effect of a freezing, of some part of the body, as the ears, fingers,
toes, or nose. Severe frostbite can lead to the loss of fingers or
toes.</def> <rj><au>Kane.</au></rj></p>

<p><ent>Frostbite</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Frostbite
<hw>Frost`bite"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To expose to the effect of
frost, or a frosty air; to blight or nip with frost.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My wife up and with Mrs. Pen to walk in the fields to
<qex>frostbite</qex> themselves.</q> <rj><qau>Pepys.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frost-bitten</ent>⟦br⟧
